        <updateDate>2020-09-18T13:16:37Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Inventor Diversity for Economic Advancement Act of 2020 or the IDEA Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) to request&nbsp;demographic information from the inventor on each patent application submitted to the USPTO.</p> <p>Inventors shall not be required to provide the requested information, which shall include gender, race, and military or veteran status.</p> <p>The USPTO shall (1) publish an annual public report about the collected data, including the collected data broken down by the types of technology covered by the patent applications; and (2) make the underlying data publicly available. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
